WEBVTT

00:00.000 --> 00:10.200
Esub's The Shepherd Boy and the Wolf

00:10.200 --> 00:14.520
retold by Jenny Dooley and Antony Kerr

00:14.520 --> 00:20.200
an express publishing storytime reader at Primary Stage 1

00:20.200 --> 00:46.760
This is Homer, a shepherd boy. He loves to play and laugh with joy.

00:46.760 --> 01:06.560
He takes the sheep to eat all day, up in the hills, as his parents say.

01:06.560 --> 01:15.600
But as he goes to work one day, he feels so bored and wants to play.

01:15.600 --> 01:35.600
What can I do? Nobody's here. How can I play? No one is near.

01:35.600 --> 01:44.400
He looks around and tries to see the other shepherds. Where can they be?

01:44.400 --> 02:02.200
I know what I can do. I'll play a game and scare them too.

02:02.200 --> 02:11.200
So he stands up and starts to cry to all the farmers who are nearby.

02:11.200 --> 02:30.800
Friends, help me. Please, come here. I'm all alone and a wolf is near.

02:30.800 --> 02:38.600
Down in the fields, the farmers stop and run to help on the hilltop.

02:38.600 --> 02:59.600
But when they go up on the hill, no wolf is there and all is still.

02:59.600 --> 03:09.600
My son, what's wrong? What happened here? The sheep are fine. No wolf is near.

03:09.600 --> 03:26.000
A wolf? There's no wolf near. It was a joke to bring you here.

03:26.000 --> 03:32.000
Come on, let's go. Our job is done. Sorry, my friends, about our son.

03:32.000 --> 03:42.000
So off they go, down the path and Homer starts to laugh and laugh.

04:02.000 --> 04:20.000
Sometimes you're happy, sometimes you're sad. But if you're bored, do not be bad.

04:20.000 --> 04:38.000
It's not very nice to have your phone when it makes things bad for everyone.

04:38.000 --> 04:47.000
When other people worry about you, do not play games that are not true.

04:47.000 --> 04:55.000
It's not very nice to have your phone when it makes things bad for everyone.

05:08.000 --> 05:37.000
Now Homer is bored. He wants to play and not to watch the sheep all day.

05:37.000 --> 05:57.000
Help me, help me. A wolf is there. He's got big teeth. He's got grey hair.

05:57.000 --> 06:07.000
The farmers stop and run up the hill, but Homer laughs. He can't keep still.

06:07.000 --> 06:17.000
There is no wolf and I scared you. It's funny, but it's not true.

06:27.000 --> 06:34.000
Homer, my boy, you are so bad. Father and I feel very mad.

06:34.000 --> 06:42.000
Homer, that's right. Why do you lie? We won't come back if we hear you cry.

06:57.000 --> 07:20.000
People hear you scream and cry. They run to help, so do not lie.

07:20.000 --> 07:30.000
Be very careful what you say. You may need help another day.

07:30.000 --> 07:37.000
You may need help another day.

07:50.000 --> 08:10.000
Homer feels sad. He doesn't like sheep. He lies on the ground and goes to sleep.

08:10.000 --> 08:34.000
Now here's a wolf. He's big. He's strong. He likes to eat sheep. His teeth are long.

08:34.000 --> 08:43.000
Homer wakes up. What does he see? His sheep aren't there. Where can they be?

08:43.000 --> 09:03.000
Help me, help me. The sheep are gone. There's a big wolf here. He's bad and strong.

09:03.000 --> 09:11.000
Down in the fields, the farmer's here. Help me, help me. A wolf is near.

09:11.000 --> 09:24.000
It's Homer again. Don't listen or run. He's such a bad boy. He's just having fun.

09:33.000 --> 09:41.000
A wolf. A wolf. The sheep are gone. His hair is grey. His teeth are long.

09:41.000 --> 09:59.000
A wolf. A wolf. It's not a lie. It's real this time. Is that why you cry?

